<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1305,1728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1558,1584]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[378,481,1557,1583]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">lectotype</typeStatus>
corresponds to the current interpretation of the species, but it also agrees with the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Comolli, 1837)" baseAuthorityName="Comolli" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[319,747,1593,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Variimorda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briantea">
<emphasis box="[319,551,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">Variimorda briantea</emphasis>
(Comolli, 1837)
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, the collection of Antonio Villa containing a single type specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Comolli" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[430,555,1629,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Variimorda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="briantea">
<emphasis box="[430,555,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">V. briantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been destroyed (
<bibRefCitation author="Bosquet, Y." box="[812,974,1629,1655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 776" refId="ref4825" refString="Bosquet, Y. (2016) Litteratura Coleopterologica (1758 - 1900): a guide to selected books related to the taxonomy of Coleoptera with publication dates and notes. ZooKeys, 583, 1 - 776. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 583.7084" type="journal article" year="2016">Bosquet 2016</bibRefCitation>
; Fabrizio Rigato, MSNM, pers. comm.). Therefore, we cannot confirm the validity of the two species here. Genitalia of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1064,1169,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Variimorda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basalis">
<emphasis box="[1064,1169,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">V. basalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1175,1278,1665,1691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">lectotype</typeStatus>
are illustrated here for the first time (
<figureCitation box="[404,535,1701,1728]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–15" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,669,1958]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14–15. Parameres of Variimorda basalis (Costa, 1854) lectotype. 14, left paramere, dorsal view. 15, right paramere, medial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3992248" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3992248/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="45">Figs 14–15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
